HEADWORD: Bristly
<hw>Bris"tly</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Thick set with
bristles, or with hairs resembling bristles; rough.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The leaves of the black mulberry are somewhat
<qex>bristly</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bristol</ent>⟦br⟧
